1
00:00:00,160 --> 00:00:01,680
I won’t have peace until Ateş is dead.

2
00:00:02,240 --> 00:00:04,280
He’ll pay for what he did with his life.

3
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:06,840
And I’m telling you, I
won’t let you harm him.

4
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:09,600
If you want to kill him,
you’ll have to kill me first.

5
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:11,240
Mercan!

6
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:15,280
Mercan!

7
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:16,520
I said let go!

8
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:17,600
Let go!

9
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:19,640
Are you asleep?

10
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,640
Haydar got right under your nose.

11
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,120
Why are you going behind my back?

12
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:27,840
I wanted to get rid of that
man. Look at the state I’m in now.

13
00:00:28,280 --> 00:00:31,360
Stay away from Ateş.

14
00:00:31,960 --> 00:00:33,080
I’ll be the one to kill him.

15
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:35,560
Congratulations on your wedding.

16
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:37,800
My gift has reached you.

17
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:41,440
Enjoy it, I hope Mercan likes it a lot.

18
00:00:42,160 --> 00:00:46,480
You won’t have a moment of peace. I’m
as close as your breath to both of you.

19
00:00:53,240 --> 00:00:54,240
Mercan!

20
00:00:58,040 --> 00:01:01,360
You've been on this journey with
Ates and Mercan from the very beginning.

21
00:01:01,680 --> 00:01:04,680
Every twist, every
heartbreak. Every moment.

22
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:07,519
And now we reach the end.

23
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:09,439
This isn't something to watch alone.

24
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:11,759
This is something we experience together.

25
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:17,320
Episodes 98, 99 and 100 will not
be available on any memberships.

26
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:20,880
They will premiere on YouTube
for all of us at the same time.

27
00:01:21,320 --> 00:01:22,399
One moment.

28
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:25,279
One story. One ending.

29
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:27,839
So grab your comfy
blanket and a huge bucket

30
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:30,840
of popcorn for one final twist.

31
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:32,920
Let's be there together.

32
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:08,720
"ONE DAY BEFORE THE 187TH DAY..."

33
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,200
Mercan.

34
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,800
Mercan.

35
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:43,800
Wake up.

36
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,880
Mercan, get up. Come on.

37
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,120
There you go.

38
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:57,120
That's it, Ms. bride-to-be.

39
00:02:57,400 --> 00:03:00,480
Off you go to wash up now, Ms. Bride-to-be.

40
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:03,840
Wake up, come on.

41
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:08,200
Sleepy head.

42
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,960
You've got to be kidding me, Mercan.

43
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:23,400
You went back to bed? I
know how I'll wake you up.

44
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:26,680
Okay, I'm up.

45
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:31,640
Come on, get up. Get up.

46
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:33,640
Come here.

47
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,760
Just five more minutes.

48
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:41,880
No, sorry.

49
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:43,640
Meanie.

50
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:49,520
If you keep whining, I'll
run a cold shower for you.

51
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:51,520
No, don't.

52
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:54,120
I'm up, look. I'm awake.

53
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:56,560
-You see. -Okay, come on.

54
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,760
I forgot to say "good morning", didn't I?

55
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:12,120
You did.

56
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,240
Good morning.

57
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:18,480
Good morning.

58
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:26,760
-Good morning. -Good morning.

59
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:32,600
Mercan? Did you just wake up?

60
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,480
I can't believe you, it's
your henna night tonight.

61
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:37,880
We have so much to do...

62
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:40,560
and you're dilly dallying.

63
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:54,280
Who is it?

64
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,720
It's from work. I'll be downstairs.

65
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:01,080
Okay.

66
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:03,040
Come on, go get ready.

67
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,480
We have so much to do, come on.

68
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,160
Hello.

69
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:13,440
We haven't had a chance
to talk in days, Ateş.

70
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,440
I thought I'd give you a call.

71
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,600
Did you like my present?

72
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,800
It was predictable.

73
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:26,920
I'd expect something
more creative from you.

74
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:28,880
I'll keep that in mind for the next one.

75
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:31,400
But, admit it.

76
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:34,360
I managed to get under your skin.

77
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:36,560
What did Mercan think of it?

78
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:39,240
Don't you dare speak her name.

79
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:43,600
She must've figured out
she'll be rid of you soon.

80
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,760
Free of your captivity.

81
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:50,280
Good luck finding me.

82
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:55,800
If you called to tell me that,
you must be getting scared.

83
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:58,120
I must be getting close.

84
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,040
You've always been a coward.

85
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:12,280
But you won't get away with this.

86
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:13,920
Relay this to Haydar, as well.

87
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:16,600
Where is he? He's been awfully quiet.

88
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,080
He's well, thanks for asking.

89
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:26,680
He's looking forward to
visiting your grave, just as I am.

90
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:31,240
Only in your dreams, keep dreaming!

91
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:35,080
We'll see if it's dream or reality, Ateş.

92
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:38,600
You won't even see me coming.

93
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:46,960
How have we still not found these men?

94
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:51,480
I don't know what to tell you,
they're nowhere to be found.

95
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:55,280
We need to find them by tomorrow.

96
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:01,440
Mercan's been on edge
since the last incident.

97
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:04,200
She's worried something's
going to happen to me.

98
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:10,240
I don't want my wife
to be anxious or upset.

99
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:25,880
If only they'd caught Nezir already.

100
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:28,040
I'd feel much more at ease.

101
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,600
Mom.

102
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,640
Could we not speak about that right now?

103
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,680
Good morning.

104
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:46,360
Good morning, Demet.

105
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,600
Your friend's lack of urgency
is driving me up the wall.

106
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,760
Tell her to get excited a little bit.

107
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,200
It's her henna night, tonight!

108
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:03,680
Mom, why don't you go downstairs
and check if the food's ready?

109
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:06,080
Okay, I'll leave.

110
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:14,680
You said you were going
to talk to him again,

111
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,280
have you had a chance?

112
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,760
I did, many times.

113
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:20,400
But he won't give up.

114
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:25,440
He's become even more
determined that package.

115
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:30,240
But I want to have neither this
henna ceremony nor the wedding.

116
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:33,080
I'm terrified something's
going to happen to Ateş.

117
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,920
Everyone's so excited.

118
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:38,560
I don't know what to do, Demet.

119
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,760
I don't want to call things
off at the last minute but...

120
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,400
there's no other choice.

121
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:47,240
It doesn't feel right when
Ateş is under such threat.

122
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:44,160
You vile man,

123
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:46,360
why did you have me
tied up like some madman?

124
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:55,680
You look so pathetic right now.

125
00:09:57,840 --> 00:09:59,680
I wish you'd accept your fate.

126
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:08,280
You're struggling in vain. You
know very well that you won't escape.

127
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,400
Just like Mercan and Ateş.

128
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:16,520
They also believe they
can escape their fate.

129
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:23,040
Stop this nonsense, Nezir. Release me!

130
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:26,080
We don't have time to play games.

131
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:28,200
We're on the same side.

132
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:30,360
We have the same enemy!

133
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:38,400
You betrayed our partnership, Haydar!

134
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:43,160
I told you time and time
again, to not go rogue.

135
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:45,240
You ruined my plan.

136
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:47,560
It will have its consequences.

137
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:53,640
I won't have any use for you soon.

138
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,320
Stop with the roundabout
talk, be straight with me.

139
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,400
Will you kill me, too?

140
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,840
Everything's possible in life, Haydar.

141
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:46,040
I have to get rid of
this guy no matter what...

142
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:49,160
or he'll burn everyone, including me.

143
00:12:48,520 --> 00:12:50,320
Good morning, Ateş. You called me?

144
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:51,600
Good morning, Burak.

145
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:53,560
We should have a talk
when Mercan gets here.

146
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:54,840
Okay.

147
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:55,920
She's here.

148
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,440
Good morning.

149
00:12:57,760 --> 00:12:59,200
-Good morning. -Is there a meeting?

150
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:03,400
The 187 days end tomorrow.

151
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:12,920
I will return everything I've taken
under my name, just as we'd agreed on.

152
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:15,680
The moment you sign the agreement...

153
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,880
everything will belong to you two.

154
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:32,400
Uhm...

155
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:34,520
There's no need for that, Ateş.

156
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:37,200
I agree.

157
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:38,720
You keep them.

158
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:41,080
That would be wrong.

159
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:43,280
It'll be just as we talked...

160
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:45,160
in line with the agreement.

161
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:49,040
Okay, if you say so.

162
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:52,480
Then, I'll go to the
company. I have things to do.

163
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:54,120
Is there anything else?

164
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:55,320
You can go.

165
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:57,240
-See you later. -See you.

166
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,600
187 days went by in the blink of an eye.

167
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:09,560
I remember the first day...

168
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:15,400
I will never forgive myself...

169
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:18,160
for everything I put you through.

170
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:20,600
You know that's not what I meant.

171
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:24,640
Every day we spent together is invaluable.

172
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:28,400
Those days make our story.

173
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:35,960
You've been in my life
since we were children.

174
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,400
Time came in-between us.

175
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,400
We were seperated but...

176
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,640
you were always here.

177
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,200
Always.

178
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:49,920
Okay, dear. Soak those
eggplants in water, let them sit.

179
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:54,680
- Are the lentil patties ready?
- They're ready, mom.

180
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:57,041
I'll get started on the
stuffed meatballs and plate them.

181
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:59,280
- Don't worry.
- How will we get it all ready in time?

182
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:02,040
How will we make it? We still
have to prepare the henna.

183
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:04,840
-We'll make it. -We won't make it in time.

184
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,600
Everyone's so excited.

185
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:11,120
Come.

186
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:15,960
-Hi, good morning. -Hi, how's it going?

187
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:19,000
- It's going well, thanks. Welcome.
- Welcome.

188
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:25,800
Our traditions are a little
different. Did mom give you the list?

189
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:27,160
Yes, she did.

190
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:31,000
I've just made the Karakus desert,
and the Tas Kadayif is ready as well.

191
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:36,400
I'm about to get started on the Baklava
with extra walnuts you requested, Mercan.

192
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:40,960
Everything will be wonderful!
Both the henna night and the wedding.

193
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:44,360
Thank you for all your hard
work. Everything smells delicious.

194
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:45,800
Hide this Kadayif, though.

195
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:48,480
Don't let Cemal see it or we
won't have any left for the night.

196
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:52,480
We'll hide it, don't you worry.

197
00:15:53,280 --> 00:15:54,440
Thank you for your hard work.

198
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,120
-Thank you. -Thanks.

199
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:05,320
- Mom, I put the eggplants in water.
- Okay, let them sit for a while.

200
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:08,040
Come on, Binnaz, you'll
make it. Keep going.

201
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:11,840
Where is Haydar?

202
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:14,760
Where could he have
hidden? Where could he be?

203
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:21,400
There's still no sign of him.

204
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,040
What if he's disappeared?

205
00:16:29,960 --> 00:16:31,320
What if he's run away?

206
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:32,800
What if I can't find him?

207
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,720
He kidnapped my son...

208
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:37,760
and killed him.

209
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:39,480
-Mom? -What if I can't find him?

210
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,680
I'm going to kill him with my bare hands.

211
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,320
-With my bare hands! -Mom!

212
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,400
Mom!

213
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:49,040
-Mom! -With my bare hands...

214
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:51,760
Mom! Breathe! Calm down.

215
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:55,360
Mom! Help!

216
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:56,760
Mom...

217
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:00,800
Mom? Mom?

218
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,400
Mom, can you hear me?

219
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:03,640
Mom?

220
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,200
Somebody help!

221
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:09,360
Mom!

222
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:11,560
What happened?

223
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:13,640
I don't know, she
collapsed all of a sudden.

224
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:14,680
Mom!

225
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:16,880
Mom!

226
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:18,920
Mom?

227
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:34,960
Mom, are you okay?

228
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:39,880
I'm okay.

229
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:42,000
I'm a little dizzy.

230
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:44,000
We should call a doctor.

231
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:45,760
I'm fine.

232
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:51,920
We should take her to the
hospital, what if it's serious?

233
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:55,520
There's no need for a doctor
or a hospital, I'm fine now.

234
00:17:56,080 --> 00:17:57,520
Mom, don't just ignore it.

235
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:58,760
What if it's serious?

236
00:17:59,040 --> 00:18:00,040
I'm fine.

237
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:02,320
I only need to lie down for a minute.

238
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:04,520
We have the henna ceremony tonight.

239
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:06,800
Forget about the ceremony, if we need to...

240
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:07,880
I'm fine.

241
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:09,520
I'm okay.

242
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:11,920
Is there something we can do?

243
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:14,880
No.

244
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:19,040
I'm here, I'll stay
with her. You should go.

245
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:21,400
Let us know if something happens.

246
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:30,120
You should let it go already, mom.

247
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,920
You're hurting yourself.

248
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:48,040
I can't rest easy until
I've taken Haydar's life.

249
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:51,600
I need to find Haydar before Ateş does.

250
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:58,840
I need to find him before Ateş.

251
00:19:03,640 --> 00:19:05,960
Mrs. Müzeyyen is still struggling.

252
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:09,040
She's been acting differently since she...

253
00:19:09,080 --> 00:19:11,000
found out she was my brother's mother.

254
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:13,440
It's not easy.

255
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:16,240
I was thinking...

256
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,040
Aslı should stay a while longer.

257
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:22,680
I'm not exactly keen on her either but...

258
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:26,680
she seems different, calmer.

259
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:28,920
Whatever you say goes...

260
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:31,120
but I can't be too sure.

261
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:35,880
I'll go check on my mom.

262
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:47,720
I expect some good news, Cemal.

263
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,560
I have the best news.

264
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:01,880
He finally talked.

265
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:03,560
We'll catch Nezir and Haydar soon.

266
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:04,960
That's what I'm talking about!

267
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,640
Send me the location right away.

268
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:09,280
Ateş...

269
00:20:10,160 --> 00:20:12,280
You're about to do something
dangerous, aren't you?

270
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:22,016
Brother, you have the henna ceremony
tonight and the wedding's tomorrow.

271
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,040
Let us handle it.

272
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:24,440
No way, Cemal.

273
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:26,920
I'll turn them in myself.

274
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:32,840
I told you to send me the address, Cemal!

275
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:34,920
Okay, Ateş. I'll send it.

276
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:44,880
I can't let you go alone.

277
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:09,120
We're at the finish line.

278
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:12,320
I'll end it all today.

279
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:40,280
I hope it turns out good.

280
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:42,120
You've tasted it, right?

281
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:44,840
- Yes, it's delicious. Don't worry.
- Okay, good.

282
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,760
How are we going to get
everything done in time?

283
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,440
Everything will be great, mom. Don't worry.

284
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,040
How will we make it?

285
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:55,480
The guys are here!

286
00:21:57,080 --> 00:21:58,120
Here you are.

287
00:21:59,080 --> 00:22:00,720
Did you get everything, son?

288
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:03,320
Yes, mom. I'll set them aside, here.

289
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:06,680
-Did you get everything, Berat? -We did.

290
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:09,120
-Good job. -I got everything you asked for.

291
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:10,760
-You asked for this. -Yes.

292
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:13,680
-Wow! -Look, it's so pretty, Çiçek.

293
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:15,040
We got this, as well, look.

294
00:22:17,840 --> 00:22:19,920
You'll entertain yourself to death.

295
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:23,160
I won't go the store a
second time, let me tell you.

296
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:25,280
I'm done.

297
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:27,480
My feet are killing me.

298
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:32,160
The rich like to indulge their
eyes before their stomachs, brother.

299
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,760
Come on, stop messing around.

300
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:43,840
We have so much to do! We have
to prepare all of this by tonight.

301
00:22:44,120 --> 00:22:45,920
I'm not doing anything else, mom.

302
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:48,920
I need to rest and have
a cup of tea, I'm beat.

303
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:50,760
Come on, Berat!

304
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:52,760
Where is Zehra?

305
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:57,600
Zehra went to tend to Mrs.
Müzeyyen. She should be back soon.

306
00:22:57,880 --> 00:22:58,880
Good.

307
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:02,720
Here she is.

308
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,560
Honey, you're back!

309
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:06,080
Yes, I just got back, honey.

310
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:11,280
Now that everyone's here,
I'd like to share some news.

311
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:13,800
-News? -What is it?

312
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:15,120
What's up?

313
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:19,280
My god, you must've heard my
prayers. Give me the good news.

314
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:21,440
Come on, tell us!

315
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:30,680
I'm pregnant!

316
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,080
Berat, I'm pregnant!

317
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:40,560
We're having a baby!

318
00:23:48,680 --> 00:23:49,720
You're pregnant?

319
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:50,760
Yes, I am.

320
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:52,200
We're having a baby?

321
00:23:52,360 --> 00:23:53,960
We're having a baby.

322
00:23:54,280 --> 00:23:55,640
-We are? -Yes.

323
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:04,840
-You're pregnant? -I'm pregnant.

324
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:08,360
-I'm going to be a dad? -Yes, you are.

325
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,560
Yes!

326
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:13,680
Careful!

327
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:18,360
Berat, calm down! Let the
girl down, she's with child!

328
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:19,440
Yes, you're right.

329
00:24:19,480 --> 00:24:20,840
-Have a seat. -Come here, dear.

330
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:21,920
Be careful!

331
00:24:22,120 --> 00:24:23,400
Have a seat, honey.

332
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:26,160
Do something.

333
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:28,160
Malik, get her tea.

334
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:29,720
Get her water, water!

335
00:24:30,040 --> 00:24:31,680
Calm down, brother.

336
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:33,280
-Have some of this. -Mom!

337
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:34,720
-No, thank you. -Have some.

338
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:35,880
Eat it, honey.

339
00:24:35,960 --> 00:24:36,960
Enjoy, dear.

340
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,560
-For strenght! -Enjoy!

341
00:24:41,520 --> 00:24:42,840
A grandmother!

342
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:45,400
- I'm going to be a grandma!
- You're going to be a grandma.

343
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:49,360
And I'm going to be an aunt.

344
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:52,000
-Auntie. -I'm going to be an aunt!

345
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:58,760
Thank you, god!

346
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:03,320
You're going to be a grandmother!

347
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:05,400
I'm going to be a grandmother!

348
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:07,960
I can't believe it!

349
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:09,480
Come on, let's dance horon!

350
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:12,080
Horon? Wait up.

351
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:14,640
-Don't you get up! -Don't you know horon?

352
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:16,400
-I don't. -Okay, come but don't jump.

353
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:19,320
Wait a minute! So, am I
going to be an uncle or what?

354
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:22,840
- You're still just an in-law.
- Yes, brother-in-law.

355
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:37,480
I'm going to be a grandmother!

356
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:42,040
God bless us.

357
00:25:46,280 --> 00:25:48,960
Çiçek, I hope you
experience the same happiness.

358
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:06,800
Hello, Demet?

359
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:08,520
Okay, I'll be there soon.

360
00:26:16,480 --> 00:26:17,760
What are you doing here?

361
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:26,360
Keep driving.

362
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:27,720
I'll put on my seatbelt.

363
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:28,800
Mercan.

364
00:26:29,720 --> 00:26:30,720
What?

365
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:33,040
You wouldn't have let
me come if I'd told you.

366
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:34,480
What do you think you're doing?

367
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:36,200
What do you think you're doing?

368
00:26:36,320 --> 00:26:38,120
You should've let the police handle it.

369
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:40,000
Those men want to kill you.

370
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:47,400
Where to?

371
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:49,080
Ateş, where are we going?

372
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:52,000
I'm going to drop you
back home and then go.

373
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:53,320
No!

374
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:54,880
Yes.

375
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:56,880
I won't let you go alone, Ateş!

376
00:26:57,280 --> 00:26:58,520
Cemal will be there.

377
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:03,760
I can't live with myself if something
happened to you, don't you understand?

378
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,720
Alright, don't cry.

379
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:13,640
Don't make me, then.

380
00:27:13,840 --> 00:27:15,280
Then, you should listen to me.

381
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:22,880
Yes?

382
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:24,520
We missed them.

383
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:28,280
You don't need to come. They
fooled us, there's no one here.

384
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:31,320
Okay.

385
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:33,280
-Go back home. -I'll be there.

386
00:27:57,520 --> 00:27:58,760
Bring it here, guys.

387
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:03,240
Put it over there.

388
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,200
Put those over here.

389
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:20,480
What's this?

390
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:24,720
The wedding chest, what else?

391
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:27,520
What do you know about...

392
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:29,480
customs and tradition, anyway?

393
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:32,040
This is our custom.

394
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:33,480
It's a tradition.

395
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:36,320
I've been working hard
to make this a wedding...

396
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:38,880
befit our dignity while
you've been sitting around.

397
00:28:40,440 --> 00:28:42,440
You never know who your
friends and enemies are.

398
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:44,680
I wouldn't want my good name sullied.

399
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:47,680
What good name you have to be sullied?

400
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:50,680
As if she's the one getting married...

401
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:55,720
Where's Mercan, Demet?

402
00:28:56,120 --> 00:28:57,600
I keep calling but can't reach her.

403
00:28:58,360 --> 00:29:00,240
She went out, she said she'd be back soon.

404
00:29:02,760 --> 00:29:04,720
What about Ateş? Where is he?

405
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:07,560
I think they're together.

406
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:10,640
Maybe they felt overwhelmed
and went out for some air.

407
00:29:23,520 --> 00:29:25,240
Where is this Mrs. Müzeyyen?

408
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:31,400
Maybe the maid knows.

409
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:42,440
I hope to hear some good news, this time.

410
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:44,080
Sorry, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

411
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:47,920
We found the warehouse Haydar
hid in but they were already gone.

412
00:29:48,240 --> 00:29:50,160
We're doing everything
in our power to find him.

413
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:52,600
We'll bring Haydar to you, don't worry.

414
00:29:53,080 --> 00:29:54,840
It doesn't seem like it.

415
00:30:02,240 --> 00:30:04,880
I can't deal with you right now.

416
00:30:07,320 --> 00:30:09,200
Where have you been, Mrs. Müzeyyen?

417
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:11,920
What are you doing here?

418
00:30:12,040 --> 00:30:13,880
I thought it was time for a reminder.

419
00:30:14,040 --> 00:30:16,480
This is neither the time
nor the place. Get out!

420
00:30:17,600 --> 00:30:20,600
I'm not going anywhere
until I get my money.

421
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:22,240
I told you.

422
00:30:22,560 --> 00:30:24,000
I'm thinking of buying a house.

423
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:28,680
The pocket money you've sent so far
is neither enough for a house or...

424
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:32,160
anything else.

425
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:36,760
I'm paying you more than
enough! Spend a little sparingly.

426
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:49,520
You expect me to live in squalor...

427
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:53,920
while you live in a
palace? There's no way.

428
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:57,280
That's enough out of you! I
told you to leave, get out!

429
00:30:59,560 --> 00:31:01,000
Who is that woman?

430
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:03,480
It looks like an argument.

431
00:31:09,440 --> 00:31:12,960
You won't get rid of me so easily.

432
00:31:13,800 --> 00:31:15,760
You either give me the money...

433
00:31:16,480 --> 00:31:19,080
or you deal with the consequences.

434
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:25,280
I have to deal with on
top of everything else?

435
00:31:26,320 --> 00:31:28,000
God give me patience.

436
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:03,160
We need to talk.

437
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:04,880
I know what you're going to say.

438
00:32:06,480 --> 00:32:08,680
We already decided we wouldn't
give him what he wanted.

439
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:11,760
That was before we received that bullet.

440
00:32:12,360 --> 00:32:13,760
Things have changed.

441
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:15,320
Nothing's changed.

442
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:16,400
It's Nezir.

443
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:18,280
He's always thrown around threats.

444
00:32:22,040 --> 00:32:24,080
We missed him by a hair!

445
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:28,600
Do we know when they left?

446
00:32:28,800 --> 00:32:30,840
He had just left, we were so close!

447
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:36,720
You don't need to hide anything from me.

448
00:32:40,480 --> 00:32:41,760
He left a note.

449
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:48,520
"You will never catch me."

450
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:50,840
We'll see about what we do to you.

451
00:33:01,440 --> 00:33:02,960
We were so close...

452
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:08,320
It's the sergeant.

453
00:33:09,360 --> 00:33:10,360
Yes?

454
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:13,280
Ateş, there's nothing more to consider.

455
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:17,560
I'd had already decided to tell everyone
tonight, that there wouldn't be a wedding.

456
00:33:19,200 --> 00:33:20,840
If you care about me...

457
00:33:21,960 --> 00:33:23,960
We figured out why
they left that warehouse.

458
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:26,080
They fled the country.

459
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:28,080
Are we certain?

460
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:29,640
That's what the sargeant told me.

461
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:32,000
There's a silver lining.

462
00:33:32,280 --> 00:33:35,560
They won't be able to meddle
in our business, at least.

463
00:33:36,760 --> 00:33:37,760
You're right.

464
00:33:38,360 --> 00:33:40,640
The police will catch
them in the meantime...

465
00:33:41,240 --> 00:33:43,040
and we can have the wedding, just us.

466
00:33:47,920 --> 00:33:49,360
Mercan, where have you been?

467
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:50,960
Where do you think?

468
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:53,120
She was looking for trouble.

469
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:01,800
I'll see you at the henna ceremony, then.

470
00:34:02,520 --> 00:34:03,520
Let's go.

471
00:34:08,560 --> 00:34:09,920
We should still be careful.

472
00:34:32,120 --> 00:34:33,600
Don't let him out of your sight.

473
00:34:34,800 --> 00:34:36,280
If he tries anything, just shoot him.

474
00:36:20,520 --> 00:36:21,520
Hello.

475
00:36:24,440 --> 00:36:26,440
Everything's going according to plan.

476
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:30,640
Wait for my call.

477
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:42,040
It's the final stride, Haydar.

478
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:46,080
We're nearing the finish line.

479
00:36:47,080 --> 00:36:48,880
But you won't get to see the line.

480
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:18,960
Mercan, how should we do your hair?

481
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:21,400
Should we put it up like this?

482
00:37:23,560 --> 00:37:24,560
What do you think?

483
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:26,800
I'm not sure.

484
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:29,320
I think it looks good.

485
00:37:30,120 --> 00:37:33,000
I could just leave it
down, this is fine too.

486
00:37:33,320 --> 00:37:34,320
What do you think?

487
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:35,480
Maybe.

488
00:37:37,640 --> 00:37:39,160
What about the makeup?

489
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:44,080
Uhm... Wait. Let me get these out.

490
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:47,000
Should we put some color on your cheeks?

491
00:37:47,200 --> 00:37:48,920
Heavy on the blush?

492
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:50,400
Yes, I think that'd be pretty.

493
00:37:51,200 --> 00:37:52,200
Alright.

494
00:37:53,640 --> 00:37:54,640
Let's see.

495
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:58,320
Let me comb through your hair first.

496
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:02,320
Like this.

497
00:39:08,040 --> 00:39:11,000
Mercan, smiling suits you so well.

498
00:39:11,440 --> 00:39:13,800
I hope you get to smile
like this your whole life.

499
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:16,600
I wish you the same, dear.

500
00:39:17,200 --> 00:39:18,200
You too.

501
00:39:23,880 --> 00:39:25,320
What are you doing, girls?

502
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:29,560
I could hear you laughing from the hall.

503
00:39:29,600 --> 00:39:32,840
Demet and I started early on the ceremony.

504
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:36,680
It's your day, dear.

505
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:41,280
I hope it's a night you
can always smile back on.

506
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:47,040
Enough with the sentimentality.
Come on, get ready.

507
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:51,320
I'll go downstairs to see
how the preparations are going.

508
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:52,440
Okay.

509
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:54,080
-See you. -See you.

510
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:41,320
Welcome.

511
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:43,640
Enjoy your evening.

512
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:49,280
Binnaz?

513
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:50,440
Is everything ready?

514
00:40:50,480 --> 00:40:52,400
Everything's ready, Mrs. Nermin.

515
00:40:53,040 --> 00:40:55,280
You put the gold coin in the henna, right?

516
00:40:55,600 --> 00:40:57,840
We did. Let's see who gets it.

517
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:00,000
Let's see.

518
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:05,720
Oh! I think she's coming.

519
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:27,800
Oh, she looks beautiful.

520
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:31,360
-God bless her. -She's so beautiful.

521
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:36,520
My beautiful girl.

522
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:38,080
You look gorgeous.

523
00:41:42,920 --> 00:41:45,960
I'm getting emotional again but
I won't cry, my makeup will run.

524
00:41:52,640 --> 00:41:54,960
I feel so nervous all of a sudden.

525
00:41:56,120 --> 00:41:58,000
I got carried away.

526
00:42:01,640 --> 00:42:03,160
Everything's ready, Mrs. Nermin.

527
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:05,400
Make a move, Çiçek. The
cover is ready, right?

528
00:42:05,440 --> 00:42:07,800
- It's ready, mom.
- Come on, then. You should go in.

529
00:42:19,920 --> 00:42:21,920
- What's going on?
- We're going to dance, come on.

530
00:42:22,080 --> 00:42:25,680
- Come on, everyone.
- Okay, then, how about...

531
00:42:29,680 --> 00:42:32,120
Come on, borther. Join in.

532
00:42:49,560 --> 00:42:50,560
Guys.

533
00:42:51,520 --> 00:42:53,960
A father-to-be is standing
before you, just so you know.

534
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:57,320
Congrats.

535
00:42:58,000 --> 00:42:59,280
Congratulations.

536
00:42:59,440 --> 00:43:00,720
-Thank you. -Berat.

537
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:03,640
Congratulations, I wish
you all health and happiness.

538
00:43:04,120 --> 00:43:05,720
Thank you, Mr. Ateş.

539
00:43:06,840 --> 00:43:07,840
I mean Mr. Tahir.

540
00:43:10,480 --> 00:43:11,480
-Berat? -Yes?

541
00:43:12,160 --> 00:43:13,840
Is it a boy or a girl?

542
00:43:14,640 --> 00:43:16,080
We just found out.

543
00:43:16,280 --> 00:43:17,520
Health and happiness is enough.

544
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:18,600
You're right.

545
00:43:18,640 --> 00:43:19,880
Congratulations, Berat.

546
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:21,840
I hope you're next, brother.

547
00:43:24,160 --> 00:43:25,640
-I'd congratulated him already. -Yes.

548
00:43:28,120 --> 00:43:29,280
How is the cig kofte?

549
00:43:29,360 --> 00:43:30,559
You could've congratulated twice.

550
00:43:30,560 --> 00:43:32,160
Should we see if it sticks to the wall?

551
00:43:32,200 --> 00:43:33,440
It's not ready yet.

552
00:43:34,200 --> 00:43:35,200
You seem distracted.

553
00:43:35,880 --> 00:43:37,200
Are you still think about Nezir?

554
00:43:38,560 --> 00:43:40,480
I have to see for myself
to believe, you know.

555
00:43:43,960 --> 00:43:45,920
I don't know what's worse,
that we missed them...

556
00:43:47,080 --> 00:43:48,080
or they escaped.

557
00:43:53,600 --> 00:43:54,600
Okay.

558
00:43:55,560 --> 00:43:59,160
I have the secret to a happy marriage.

559
00:44:00,360 --> 00:44:01,440
Mr. Ateş Tahir.

560
00:44:02,480 --> 00:44:06,080
You need to be stern from the start.

561
00:44:10,120 --> 00:44:11,880
You should always have
the last word, right?

562
00:44:12,520 --> 00:44:15,240
Of course and the last
word is "As you wish, honey."

563
00:44:17,200 --> 00:44:18,200
Do you see?

564
00:44:18,320 --> 00:44:20,040
He's an expert on marriage now.

565
00:44:21,440 --> 00:44:22,760
We know what we're talking about.

566
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:27,640
You should listen, you may need the advice.

567
00:44:27,960 --> 00:44:28,960
Me?

568
00:44:30,360 --> 00:44:32,160
You seem to be getting
along well with Demet.

569
00:44:33,880 --> 00:44:36,720
Demet is... a good
person. She's nice and...

570
00:44:37,400 --> 00:44:39,280
we get along well.
It's nice to talk to her.

571
00:44:44,520 --> 00:44:46,000
It's starting, I think.

572
00:44:46,680 --> 00:44:48,080
We'll crash it soon.

573
00:44:49,120 --> 00:44:50,560
The groom should show himself.

574
00:44:53,040 --> 00:44:54,720
We should test it...

575
00:44:55,360 --> 00:44:56,360
to see if it's ready.

576
00:44:57,040 --> 00:44:58,920
- Let's see if it sticks to the wall.
- Let's.

577
00:44:59,840 --> 00:45:01,120
It would get dirty...

578
00:45:01,560 --> 00:45:03,240
It'll be fine, it should work.

579
00:45:07,480 --> 00:45:10,080
What would your people
know about cig kofte, anyway?

580
00:45:10,480 --> 00:45:11,640
It must be missing something.

581
00:45:12,040 --> 00:45:13,400
It's missing a lot, I think.

582
00:45:14,200 --> 00:45:15,800
Does it taste good?

583
00:45:17,120 --> 00:45:18,560
I added my love into it.

584
00:45:18,680 --> 00:45:20,280
-Obviously. -We can tell.

585
00:45:25,240 --> 00:45:27,200
Come here, Ms. Bride-to-be. Have a seat.

586
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:35,200
Come on, bring the cover.

587
00:46:43,080 --> 00:46:45,320
Bring out the henna, everything's ready.

588
00:48:25,360 --> 00:48:26,360
Are you ready?

589
00:48:26,920 --> 00:48:28,440
Give me your palm.

590
00:48:34,320 --> 00:48:37,280
The bride won't give her palm, ladies!

591
00:48:40,920 --> 00:48:41,920
You see...

592
00:48:45,000 --> 00:48:46,680
Go ahead, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

593
00:48:52,360 --> 00:48:53,360
Open.

594
00:49:12,600 --> 00:49:13,600
Come here.

595
00:49:28,640 --> 00:49:30,800
I wish you a long and happy marriage.

596
00:49:36,400 --> 00:49:39,920
I found it! I found the gold coin.

597
00:49:43,840 --> 00:49:45,440
I got the gold!

598
00:49:45,520 --> 00:49:48,920
We have out next bride.

599
00:51:47,600 --> 00:51:48,800
Don't cry, dear.

600
00:51:51,600 --> 00:51:53,360
These are tears of happiness.

601
00:51:54,800 --> 00:51:57,040
You'll only shed tears
of happiness from now on.

602
00:52:00,280 --> 00:52:01,280
Pretty eyes.

603
00:52:03,360 --> 00:52:04,480
Pearly Mercan.

604
00:52:07,640 --> 00:52:09,160
You look beautiful.

605
00:52:10,120 --> 00:52:11,120
Thank you.

606
00:52:11,720 --> 00:52:12,880
You look great.

607
00:52:14,040 --> 00:52:15,320
Are you excited?

608
00:52:15,880 --> 00:52:17,040
Very.

609
00:52:17,320 --> 00:52:23,720
-She looks so beautiful. -They're so sweet.

610
00:52:23,880 --> 00:52:28,600
Mr. Groom, have a seat next to the
bride and we'll get your henna as well.

611
00:52:29,280 --> 00:52:30,280
Come on.

612
00:52:38,080 --> 00:52:41,720
Let us apply your henna, Mr. Groom.

613
00:53:05,640 --> 00:53:08,120
I wish you a long and happy marriage.

614
00:53:17,240 --> 00:53:18,520
I love you so much.

615
00:53:20,440 --> 00:53:22,040
I love you the most.

616
00:53:22,680 --> 00:53:24,360
More than anything else.

617
00:53:26,160 --> 00:53:27,520
I love you so much.

618
00:53:28,880 --> 00:53:30,160
You're my peace.

619
00:53:30,800 --> 00:53:32,240
You're invaluable.

620
00:55:16,720 --> 00:55:19,280
Play us something we can dance to, come on!

621
00:58:00,840 --> 00:58:02,880
May the men step outside?

622
00:58:03,760 --> 00:58:05,920
-Come on. -Come on, brother. Demet's right.

623
00:58:06,440 --> 00:58:07,680
I'll miss you.

624
00:58:08,480 --> 00:58:10,000
I miss you already.

625
00:58:11,640 --> 00:58:12,640
Come on.

626
00:58:12,840 --> 00:58:13,960
Demet's right.

627
00:58:14,120 --> 00:58:15,120
You should step out.

628
00:58:15,280 --> 00:58:16,960
You can't see the bride until the wedding.

629
00:58:17,320 --> 00:58:18,440
Come on, Ateş.

630
00:58:18,960 --> 00:58:21,200
Let me come with you,
I'll get some fresh air.

631
00:58:21,440 --> 00:58:29,160
-No way! -Be a good sport, come on.

632
00:58:29,280 --> 00:58:33,520
- Where are you going?
- You need to stay apart until the wedding.

633
00:58:33,600 --> 00:58:38,720
-Come on! -Come on, brother!

634
00:58:38,840 --> 00:58:46,840
-Come on! -Let's go, be a good sport!

635
00:58:51,800 --> 00:58:56,280
Come on, Ms. Bride. Dance away the night!

636
01:00:18,880 --> 01:00:19,880
Wait up!

637
01:00:20,760 --> 01:00:22,040
What's going on?

638
01:00:22,520 --> 01:00:24,880
We told you, you can't see
the groom before the wedding.

639
01:00:25,920 --> 01:00:28,320
Don't be ridiculous, we're already married.

640
01:00:29,200 --> 01:00:31,440
Stop complaining, we didn't make the...

641
01:00:31,480 --> 01:00:34,280
decision to have a
second wedding, you did.

642
01:00:52,240 --> 01:00:54,680
The guys are having a feast in the office.

643
01:00:57,240 --> 01:01:01,720
We should have a feast of our own if
we're spending the night just us girls.

644
01:01:02,240 --> 01:01:03,240
Girls' night!

645
01:01:05,080 --> 01:01:08,120
Okay, then. I'll go get changed.

646
01:01:08,520 --> 01:01:09,520
Okay.

647
01:01:14,840 --> 01:01:18,880
You should go to the kitchen and
begin, I'll change and come to help.

648
01:01:19,480 --> 01:01:21,520
Okay, I'll be down at the kitchen.

649
01:01:21,880 --> 01:01:22,880
Okay.

650
01:01:52,840 --> 01:01:54,520
I'm here, don't worry.

651
01:01:54,680 --> 01:01:57,040
I'm here. We'll go down
to the kitchen later.

652
01:01:58,720 --> 01:01:59,720
Demet.

653
01:02:00,320 --> 01:02:02,600
Keep moving, come on.

654
01:02:03,040 --> 01:02:04,040
Keep moving!

655
01:02:04,440 --> 01:02:05,440
Come on.

656
01:02:30,400 --> 01:02:31,600
What's this?

657
01:02:34,920 --> 01:02:37,200
They turned the room
into a guys' dormitory.

658
01:03:20,320 --> 01:03:21,840
Stop! Where to, brother?

659
01:03:25,240 --> 01:03:27,080
I guess you didn't take us seriously...

660
01:03:28,520 --> 01:03:29,840
Cemal, move out of the way.

661
01:03:29,920 --> 01:03:32,600
No, it's tradition. You can't
see the bride before the wedding.

662
01:03:32,720 --> 01:03:34,440
-I said move, Cemal. -No way.

663
01:03:35,280 --> 01:03:36,440
Mr. Ateş, you can't!

664
01:03:37,080 --> 01:03:39,680
The bride and the groom can't
see each other before the wedding.

665
01:03:41,800 --> 01:03:43,040
You should have a seat.

666
01:03:43,600 --> 01:03:45,840
He woke up just to give us his two cents.

667
01:03:46,240 --> 01:03:47,440
This is ridiculous.

668
01:03:51,800 --> 01:03:53,400
I'll get you something to drink.

669
01:03:54,800 --> 01:03:55,800
No, thanks.

670
01:04:17,960 --> 01:04:19,360
They still haven't gone to bed.

671
01:04:23,760 --> 01:04:24,760
Neither have the guys.

672
01:04:32,800 --> 01:04:34,440
How will we see each other?

673
01:04:41,320 --> 01:04:42,320
We'll run.

674
01:04:52,040 --> 01:04:54,280
In five minutes on the kitchen porch.

675
01:04:57,600 --> 01:04:58,800
Not a second longer.

676
01:05:09,360 --> 01:05:11,240
She must be texting Ateş.

677
01:05:16,080 --> 01:05:17,320
Yes, I am, so?

678
01:05:18,520 --> 01:05:19,760
You can't, it's not right.

679
01:05:22,040 --> 01:05:23,600
Like you never see him.

680
01:05:24,440 --> 01:05:25,680
Your friend is here.

681
01:05:30,440 --> 01:05:33,680
Well, I'm beat. I wish
you girls a good night.

682
01:05:35,320 --> 01:05:38,840
You should go to bed,
we'll be up early tomorrow.

683
01:05:40,960 --> 01:05:42,800
-Good night. -Good night, mom.

684
01:05:52,600 --> 01:05:55,640
I've had enough, man! What is this?

685
01:05:56,760 --> 01:05:59,280
Wake up, man! What are you doing?

686
01:06:01,480 --> 01:06:03,400
I've had enough of your snoring!

687
01:06:05,240 --> 01:06:06,240
Enough!

688
01:06:06,360 --> 01:06:08,680
You've turned this place into a farm!

689
01:06:12,840 --> 01:06:14,120
What's going on?

690
01:06:15,960 --> 01:06:19,360
Get up. Move. I can't sleep
with your snoring, get up!

691
01:06:19,400 --> 01:06:21,120
Cemal, leave me be. I want to sleep.

692
01:06:21,200 --> 01:06:22,200
Get up.

693
01:06:25,080 --> 01:06:27,600
Come here, get out. Go to your room.

694
01:06:27,720 --> 01:06:30,536
- Find some place else to sleep, I can't stand your snoring.
- Let me get my coat.

695
01:06:30,560 --> 01:06:32,560
Okay, get your coat and leave.

696
01:06:35,240 --> 01:06:37,240
I'm talking to you, too. Get up.

697
01:06:39,240 --> 01:06:41,640
Cemal, it's comfortable
here, there's nowhere else...

698
01:06:41,680 --> 01:06:42,840
You'll find elsewhere.

699
01:06:43,680 --> 01:06:44,680
Mr. Cemal...

700
01:06:45,480 --> 01:06:46,480
Mr. Cemal!

701
01:06:46,640 --> 01:06:47,960
Keep your eyes on him.

702
01:06:48,040 --> 01:06:49,600
Don't let him see the bride.

703
01:06:50,240 --> 01:06:51,920
God give me patience.

704
01:06:57,080 --> 01:06:58,720
Do you see what I have to deal with?

705
01:07:01,040 --> 01:07:04,440
I'm starving. I'm going to get
something to eat, do you want anything?

706
01:07:06,280 --> 01:07:07,440
No, thanks. I'm fine.

707
01:07:08,040 --> 01:07:09,920
You should eat for once...

708
01:07:41,800 --> 01:07:43,080
I'm going to get some coffee.

709
01:07:43,840 --> 01:07:45,440
Where are you off to?

710
01:07:45,480 --> 01:07:47,160
I'll get you the coffee.

711
01:07:48,040 --> 01:07:49,040
No, thanks.

712
01:07:50,040 --> 01:07:51,240
What a friend you are...

713
01:08:08,400 --> 01:08:09,840
It's now or never.

714
01:09:15,520 --> 01:09:17,160
Here is the person I was looking for.

715
01:09:18,320 --> 01:09:19,320
Haydar!

716
01:09:19,800 --> 01:09:21,600
I have a wonderful surprise for you.

717
01:09:29,120 --> 01:09:30,120
Haydar.

718
01:09:31,160 --> 01:09:33,440
I finally have you in my palm!

719
01:09:48,840 --> 01:09:49,960
Mrs. Müzeyyen.

720
01:09:50,920 --> 01:09:51,920
Slow down.

721
01:09:55,720 --> 01:09:57,000
First, the deal.

722
01:10:20,800 --> 01:10:23,680
I barely escaped Demet! She
didn't look away for a second.

723
01:10:23,920 --> 01:10:25,360
I was in a similar situation.

724
01:10:25,720 --> 01:10:27,440
I escaped the moment I could.

725
01:10:28,000 --> 01:10:29,560
Did you have fun, at least?

726
01:10:29,760 --> 01:10:31,320
If you could call it fun.

727
01:10:31,440 --> 01:10:36,920
Berat kept sayin "I'm going to be
a dad." and Malik kept saying Çiçek.

728
01:10:37,160 --> 01:10:38,200
That's all.

729
01:10:38,240 --> 01:10:39,440
He's just in love.

730
01:10:40,320 --> 01:10:45,640
Then, I had to listen to Yaşar's travel
stories and Burak's military stories.

731
01:10:47,120 --> 01:10:48,320
What about you?

732
01:10:48,640 --> 01:10:53,160
We just danced and had
fun but I'm exhausted.

733
01:10:53,880 --> 01:10:54,880
You are?

734
01:10:55,840 --> 01:10:56,840
You're exhausted?

735
01:10:57,280 --> 01:10:58,600
Would you like some coffee?

736
01:10:58,680 --> 01:10:59,720
No.

737
01:11:00,000 --> 01:11:01,000
Well... What about tea?

738
01:11:01,920 --> 01:11:02,920
No, thanks.

739
01:11:03,080 --> 01:11:04,160
Milk?

740
01:11:07,080 --> 01:11:08,160
I missed you so much.

741
01:11:09,880 --> 01:11:10,880
Me too.

742
01:11:19,800 --> 01:11:21,760
I don't know if I can wait until tomorrow.

743
01:11:25,520 --> 01:11:28,160
I'll think of you until morning.

744
01:11:34,880 --> 01:11:36,160
I'll be patient.

745
01:11:36,840 --> 01:11:38,200
Because you're worth it.

746
01:11:48,440 --> 01:11:50,520
She disappeared in the blink of an eye.

747
01:12:03,280 --> 01:12:04,760
You can't find Mercan, right?

748
01:12:05,480 --> 01:12:06,480
They ran.

749
01:12:07,240 --> 01:12:08,760
It's a surprise they lasted so long.

750
01:12:09,960 --> 01:12:11,560
We didn't get to see each other today.

751
01:12:12,480 --> 01:12:14,760
It's the night before, I had a lot to do.

752
01:12:16,080 --> 01:12:17,440
It'll be the same tomorrow.

753
01:12:18,720 --> 01:12:21,880
Yes but after the wedding, I
think we'll all have time to relax.

754
01:12:25,960 --> 01:12:26,960
We will.

755
01:12:27,720 --> 01:12:29,240
Uhm... Demet, I...

756
01:12:30,920 --> 01:12:31,920
Yes?

757
01:12:35,040 --> 01:12:36,040
I...

758
01:12:41,920 --> 01:12:43,480
I think I know where they are.

759
01:12:49,840 --> 01:12:50,840
You do?

760
01:12:51,320 --> 01:12:53,120
Let's go get our fugitives, then.

761
01:12:56,000 --> 01:12:57,560
Let's give them five more minutes.

762
01:13:00,480 --> 01:13:01,880
We'll have a walk ourselves.

763
01:13:04,000 --> 01:13:05,000
Okay.

764
01:13:24,640 --> 01:13:26,160
My longing for you ends tomorrow.

765
01:13:27,400 --> 01:13:28,440
I miss you so much.

766
01:13:31,840 --> 01:13:33,480
I miss your voice when you don't talk...

767
01:13:34,360 --> 01:13:36,040
and your eyes when I can't see them.

768
01:13:37,200 --> 01:13:40,160
Your hair, your scent, your
temper... I miss all of you.

769
01:13:43,080 --> 01:13:44,840
There's not a moment I don't miss you.

770
01:13:46,760 --> 01:13:48,040
I feel the same.

771
01:14:04,440 --> 01:14:07,080
Did you think you could get away from us?

772
01:14:07,720 --> 01:14:09,640
Can't we get five minutes free from you?

773
01:14:09,920 --> 01:14:11,280
What kind of friends are you?

774
01:14:12,120 --> 01:14:13,840
Stop whining, Ms. Bride.

775
01:14:14,160 --> 01:14:17,400
Mr. Groom, step aside. You stay there.

776
01:14:19,880 --> 01:14:22,680
It's just for one night you need
to stay apart. Have some patience.

777
01:14:23,280 --> 01:14:26,240
You'll be together for a lifetime
after tomorrow, no one can seperate you.

778
01:14:29,600 --> 01:14:31,960
What kind of tradition
is this, it's ridiculous.

779
01:14:32,680 --> 01:14:35,560
I agree. What's wrong
with us staying together?

780
01:14:35,640 --> 01:14:36,720
Yes.

781
01:14:36,920 --> 01:14:39,560
Our forefathers must
know something we don't.

782
01:14:40,160 --> 01:14:41,720
I'll do the same to you.

783
01:14:43,480 --> 01:14:44,480
I agree.

784
01:14:44,520 --> 01:14:45,800
We'll do the same to them.

785
01:14:51,120 --> 01:14:56,320
Okay, sorry. We're not in a hurry.
You can say good night to each other.

786
01:15:00,440 --> 01:15:01,800
We'll be outside.

787
01:15:02,240 --> 01:15:03,400
Keep it short.

788
01:15:19,000 --> 01:15:20,600
I'm going to help you tomorrow...

789
01:15:27,240 --> 01:15:29,680
and you're going to
deliver this vile dog to me.

790
01:15:37,480 --> 01:15:41,120
Do whatever you want to whoever
you want but you won't touch Ateş.

791
01:15:41,480 --> 01:15:43,120
Or the deal's off.

792
01:15:44,160 --> 01:15:45,280
Mrs. Müzeyyen.

793
01:15:49,160 --> 01:15:50,160
Ateş, again?

794
01:15:52,800 --> 01:15:56,600
I told you before, I
have no problem with Ateş.

795
01:15:58,960 --> 01:16:00,520
I have no intention of killing him.

796
01:16:04,520 --> 01:16:05,880
I'm only concerned with Mercan.

797
01:16:15,760 --> 01:16:17,040
Mercan is yours.

